wiki.text:
'UFR' may refer to :
* Under Frequency Relay, a type of protective relay used to trip an electrical
  line when its operating frequency drops below a certain threshold.
* Unité de formation et de recherche (Unit of Formation and Research), a faculty
  in French universities and some others (University of Ouagadougou)
* Union des Forces pour le Renouveau (Union of the Renewal Forces), a political
  party in Burkina Faso
* Ultimate Fighting Revolution, a Martial arts tournament
* Union of Resistance Forces, rebel group in Chad
* Ultra Fast Rendering, a printer language
* Université de Franche-Comté, a University in eastern France
